<a href="https://github.com/zmartzone/mod_auth_openidc">mod_auth_openidc</a> makes it easy to secure your applications running in Apache or when Apache is used as a reverse proxy. It can be used both for enabling SSO to web applications as well as to secure RESTful services. For more details check out <a href="http://www.keycloak.org/docs/latest/securing_apps/index.html#_mod_auth_openidc">our documentation</a> as well as <a href="https://github.com/zmartzone/mod_auth_openidc/wiki/Keycloak">the guides from mod_auth_openidc</a>.
